<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6821003" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6821003" box="[136,1109,1525,1547]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6821003/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" startId="2.[136,229,1525,1547]" targetBox="[138,1449,190,1501]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1109,1525,1547]" box="[136,1109,1525,1547]" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,247,1525,1547]" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">FIGURE 2</emphasis>
. Lectotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Guss." authorityName="Guss." box="[387,593,1525,1547]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Meum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis box="[387,532,1526,1547]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">Meum segetum</emphasis>
Guss.
</taxonomicName>
(NAP, Gussone Sicilia Collection [without number]).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1595,1835]" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis box="[189,368,1596,1619]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">Taxonomic note:</emphasis>
It is definitely clear that 
<taxonomicName box="[645,807,1596,1619]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Meum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis box="[645,807,1596,1619]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">Meum segetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus (1771: 219)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="219" authorityYear="1771" box="[1020,1451,1595,1619]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Anethum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis box="[1020,1210,1595,1619]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">Anethum segetum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[1219,1451,1595,1619]" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" refId="ref1958" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1771) Mantissa Plantarum Altera. Generum editionis VI &amp; specierum editionis II. Holmiae [Stockholm], 587 pp." type="book" year="1771">Linnaeus (1771: 219)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(typified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jarvis, C. E. &amp; Reduron, J. P. &amp; Spencer, M. A. &amp; Cafferty, S." box="[271,458,1631,1655]" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" pagination="207 - 216" refId="ref1821" refString="Jarvis, C. E., Reduron, J. P., Spencer, M. A. &amp; Cafferty, S. (2006) Typification of Linnaean plant names in Apiaceae. Taxon 55: 207 - 216." type="journal article" year="2006">
Jarvis 
<emphasis box="[342,397,1631,1655]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
and by the same authors considered synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[999,1219,1631,1655]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Anethum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graveolens">
<emphasis box="[999,1219,1631,1655]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">Anethum graveolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.), and that it is the basionym of the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moris" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Gussone" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[380,559,1667,1691]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Ridolfia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis box="[380,559,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">Ridolfia segetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
proposed by Moris (as correctly reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hand, R." box="[1044,1165,1667,1691]" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" refId="ref1737" refString="Hand, R. (2011) Apiaceae. In: Euro + Med Plantbase - the information resource for Euro-Mediterranean plant diversity. Published on the Internet http: // ww 2. bgbm. org / EuroPlusMed / (accessed 5 March 2022)" type="url" year="2011">Hand 2011</bibRefCitation>
). This also to complete the synonyms reported in 
<bibRefCitation author="Frankiewicz, K. E. &amp; Banasiak, L. &amp; Oskolski, A. &amp; Reduron, J. &amp; Reyes-Betancort, J. A. &amp; Alsarraf, M. &amp; Trzeciak, P. &amp; Spalik, K." box="[371,640,1703,1727]" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref1589" refString="Frankiewicz, K. E., Banasiak, L., Oskolski, A., Reduron, J., Reyes-Betancort, J. A., Alsarraf, M., Trzeciak, P. &amp; Spalik, K. (2021) Longdistance dispersal events rather than growth habit and life-history traits affect diversification rate in tribe Apieae (Apiaceae). Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 198 (1): 1 - 25. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / botlinnean / boab 032" type="journal article" year="2021">
Frankiewicz 
<emphasis box="[509,555,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">et al</emphasis>
. (2021)
</bibRefCitation>
, where 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moris" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Gussone" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[721,900,1703,1727]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Ridolfia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis box="[721,900,1703,1727]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">Ridolfia segetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is reported as the basionym (and the only synonym) of the new name 
<taxonomicName authority="Spalik &amp; Reduron." authorityName="Spalik &amp; Reduron." box="[316,703,1739,1763]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Anethum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ridolfia">
<emphasis box="[316,497,1739,1763]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">Anethum ridolfia</emphasis>
Spalik &amp; Reduron.
</taxonomicName>
The main character differentiating 
<taxonomicName box="[1075,1256,1739,1763]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Anethum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ridolfia">
<emphasis box="[1075,1256,1739,1763]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">Anethum ridolfia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(≡ 
<taxonomicName box="[1291,1451,1740,1763]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Meum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis box="[1291,1451,1740,1763]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">Meum segetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
≡ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moris" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Gussone" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[157,337,1775,1799]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Ridolfia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis box="[157,337,1775,1799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">Ridolfia segetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[410,628,1775,1799]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Anethum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="graveolens">
<emphasis box="[410,628,1775,1799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">Anethum graveolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1771" box="[665,853,1775,1799]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Anethum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="segetum">
<emphasis box="[665,853,1775,1799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="208">Anethum segetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is the fruit, smooth and without ribs in the former, with three ribs in the latter.
</paragraph>
